EB_1-LojC.m3u8", "aspectRatio": [679, 540], "heightRatio": 79, "type": "video/mp4", "url": "https://video.twimg.com/amplify_video/2055462644392267777/vid/avc1/338x270/RN9EJ_ISQklm96Kl.mp4"}, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/798632247762948096/ycGYVWvr_normal.jpg", "displayName": "Alex Jones", "username": "RealAlexJones"}, "content": "THIS JUST IN- Chud the Builder has successfully raised enough donations to pay 10% of his $1.25 million bond to be released from jail.", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 56}}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASsUQNzlx", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 21, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "apu", "id": 8621619, "raw_content": "Predicting the next word is not intelligence; it's just a statistical game that proffers seemingly intelligible outputs.\n\nThe temptation of many seems to be to treat AI as they treat the media--point to them as validation when they support your theses but reject them as flawed and corrupt as soon as their voice diverges from your own.\n\nThis is a mistake and a deception.  \n\nEither a source is reliable or it's not.  An unreliable source can deliver reliable information, but it still shouldn't be believed.  LLMs don't think; they merely predict words, often creating complete hallucinations they submit to users as reality.\n\nWhen the AI bubble pops, the Fed is going to print SO MUCH MONEY.\n\nPrepare yourself with hard assets to ride the next wave of inflation.", "author": "Jaunty_Haul", "created": 1778937818966, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "SHILL_DETECTOR", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "LLM AIs are retarded.", "last_comment_created": 1778947649604, "content": "<p>Predicting the next word is not intelligence; it's just a statistical game that proffers seemingly intelligible outputs.</p>\n<p>The temptation of many seems to be to treat AI as they treat the media--point to them as validation when they support your theses but reject them as flawed and corrupt as soon as their voice diverges from your own.</p>\n<p>This is a mistake and a deception.</p>\n<p>Either a source is reliable or it's not.  An unreliable source can deliver reliable information, but it still shouldn't be believed.  LLMs don't think; they merely predict words, often creating complete hallucinations they submit to users as reality.</p>\n<p>When the AI bubble pops, the Fed is going to print SO MUCH MONEY.</p>\n<p>Prepare yourself with hard assets to ride the next wave of inflation.</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 13, "score_up": 21, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "BE\u00a0\u00a0LESS\u00a0\u00a0RETARDED", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASsUQOH1J", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 17, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "media", "id": 8621745, "raw_content": "", "author": "TEXinLA", "created": 1778941651081, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "charwoman", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "redstate.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASsUQOH1J.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://redstate.com/wardclark/2026/05/15/eric-trump-slams-psakis-monolog-of-lies-threatens-massi